.TH btctax-update-prices 1  btctax "btctax manual"
.SH NAME
btctax\-update\-prices \- Opt\-in online updater that fetches newer daily BTC/USD closes into a local cache for the btctax Bitcoin tax ledger. The ONLY btctax crate with a network dependency.
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbtctax\-update\-prices\fR [\fB\-\-from\fR] [\fB\-\-to\fR] [\fB\-\-lag\fR] [\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-\-source\fR] [\fB\-\-price\-cache\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opt\-in online updater that fetches newer daily BTC/USD closes into a local cache for the btctax Bitcoin tax ledger. The ONLY btctax crate with a network dependency.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-from\fR \fI<FROM>\fR
First date to fetch (YYYY\-MM\-DD). Default: the day after the last known close
.TP
\fB\-\-to\fR \fI<TO>\fR
Last date to fetch (YYYY\-MM\-DD). Default: today − <lag> days
.TP
\fB\-\-lag\fR \fI<LAG>\fR [default: 8]
Skip the N most recent days (the settling window; sources revise recent closes for ~7 days)
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Preview what WOULD be appended; write nothing
.TP
\fB\-\-source\fR \fI<SOURCE>\fR [default: auto]
Price source (`auto` = Binance then CoinGecko fallback)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto: Binance first, CoinGecko fallback (the default)
.IP \(bu 2
binance: Binance klines only
.IP \(bu 2
coingecko: CoinGecko market_chart/range only
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-price\-cache\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Override the cache path (default: $BTCTAX_PRICE_CACHE, else <data_dir>/btctax/price_cache.csv)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH VERSION
v0.6.0
